WEBVTT

00:57.200 --> 00:59.199
Dario!

00:59.200 --> 01:01.200
A message from Peligro.

01:08.400 --> 01:10.200
Ho!

01:28.400 --> 01:31.200
Mambo, Mambo, Mambo, Mambo.

01:31.300 --> 01:33.200
Mambo, Mambo, Mambo, Mambo.

01:33.300 --> 01:35.300
Mambo, Mambo, Mambo, Mambo.

01:36.200 --> 01:38.200
Mambo, Mambo, Mambo, Mambo.

02:38.400 --> 02:41.300
Mambo, Mambo, Mambo, Mambo.

02:41.400 --> 02:43.300
Mambo, Mambo, Mambo, Mambo.

02:43.400 --> 02:45.399
Mambo, Mambo, Mambo, Mambo.

02:45.400 --> 02:48.200
Mambo, Mambo, Mambo, Mambo.

02:57.300 --> 02:59.300
Mambo, Mambo, Mambo, Mambo.

02:59.400 --> 03:01.399
Mambo, Mambo, Mambo, Mambo.

03:01.400 --> 03:04.199
Mambo, Mambo, Mambo, Mambo.

03:04.200 --> 03:06.300
Mambo, Mambo, Mambo, Mambo.

03:14.400 --> 03:16.300
Mambo.

03:22.300 --> 03:24.400
Ladies and gentlemen,

03:24.500 --> 03:27.300
a very good evening to you all.

03:27.400 --> 03:29.300
El Tropico,

03:29.400 --> 03:32.199
the most fabulous nightclub
in the World, presents

03:32.200 --> 03:35.199
its latest, but not late show,

03:35.200 --> 03:37.299
Where we are taking you all
to the magical productions

03:37.300 --> 03:40.300
of our Rodney the Great.

03:43.400 --> 03:44.400
Ladies and gentlemen,

03:44.401 --> 03:46.400
We are honored tonight
to have in our presence

03:47.200 --> 03:49.200
the World's greatest
living race car driver,

03:49.300 --> 03:51.500
here in Cuba for the
first Havana Grand Prix.

03:52.300 --> 03:53.300
Ladies and gentlemen,

03:53.301 --> 03:56.400
the one and only Fangio
for once, stationary.

03:56.500 --> 04:00.399
Fangio! Fangio! Fangio! Fangio!

04:00.400 --> 04:02.299
Fangio!

04:02.300 --> 04:05.300
And now, a special treat

04:05.500 --> 04:07.400
for a very special couple.

04:07.500 --> 04:09.299
Forever newlyweds,

04:09.300 --> 04:12.400
Dona Cecilia, Don Federico,

04:13.200 --> 04:15.300
The Anniversary Waltz by Strauss.

04:15.400 --> 04:18.399
Happy Anniversary.

04:26.200 --> 04:26.500
A toast.

04:27.300 --> 04:29.200
To the most elegant couple in Havana.

04:29.300 --> 04:30.200
Happy Anniversary.

04:30.300 --> 04:31.300
And to this,

04:31.400 --> 04:33.300
the happiest of families.

04:33.400 --> 04:35.299
May it be that way forever.

04:35.300 --> 04:37.299
Hear, hear. Salud.

04:37.300 --> 04:38.500
Salud. Salud.

04:41.300 --> 04:43.499
Dance with me, as you once did?

04:43.500 --> 04:46.200
You make me sound like a relic.

04:46.300 --> 04:49.300
My relic.

04:50.300 --> 04:52.400
Donoso, would you dance with me?

04:53.200 --> 04:54.200
Watch yourself.

04:54.400 --> 04:56.200
Uncle has two left feet now.

04:56.300 --> 04:57.399
His elbow, it works fine.

04:57.400 --> 05:01.399
I would give an arm and
a leg and an elbow

05:01.400 --> 05:04.299
for just one single waltz.

05:04.300 --> 05:09.200
My kingdom for a cha-cha-cha!

05:09.300 --> 05:10.300
Hear, hear.

05:10.301 --> 05:12.400
Let's go dance.

05:13.500 --> 05:16.400
I'll be right back. Wait here.

05:24.400 --> 05:25.400
What's wrong?

05:27.400 --> 05:30.299
So which one of those dancers

05:30.300 --> 05:31.300
is your girlfriend this week?

05:34.300 --> 05:36.300
Who are you saving yourself for?

05:36.400 --> 05:38.299
No one.

05:38.300 --> 05:40.300
All the good ones are already spoken for.

05:42.400 --> 05:43.300
Fangio, I want to present to you

05:43.400 --> 05:45.300
my wife Mercedes Fellove.

05:54.200 --> 05:55.400
Come on, let's go.

05:59.500 --> 06:04.199
This meeting was my idea...

06:04.200 --> 06:08.400
because these are very
difficult times, as you know.

06:08.500 --> 06:10.399
Cuba has always lived in difficult times,

06:10.400 --> 06:13.399
but through them all, we
have been able to survive

06:13.400 --> 06:18.299
because we have always been united.

06:18.300 --> 06:21.299
But our country isn't safe anymore,

06:21.300 --> 06:24.400
and it threatens us.

06:24.500 --> 06:30.200
Your uncle and I are all that
remains of our generation.

06:32.300 --> 06:37.499
So, my sons, you are the future.

06:37.500 --> 06:40.200
The future of our family.

06:40.400 --> 06:42.200
The future of this island.

06:42.400 --> 06:46.299
Yes, and look at me.

06:46.300 --> 06:48.300
Look at me, because this is for you, too.

06:48.400 --> 06:51.299
If we want to change the status quo,

06:51.300 --> 06:55.300
we must go about it in a democratic way.

06:55.400 --> 06:56.499
You hear?

06:56.500 --> 06:58.399
We must be patriots.

06:58.400 --> 06:59.400
Patriots.

07:00.200 --> 07:02.399
Patriotism is a refuge for scoundrels.

07:02.400 --> 07:04.199
Do you

07:04.200 --> 07:05.299
Lt is politics that has become

07:05.300 --> 07:07.299
the practical refuge of.

07:07.300 --> 07:08.499
Papi, do not make the mistake

07:08.500 --> 07:10.299
of confusing me for one of your students.

07:10.300 --> 07:11.300
I'm not. I graduated.

07:11.300 --> 07:12.300
Hey.

07:12.301 --> 07:15.299
Show a little respect.

07:15.300 --> 07:17.399
No, no, no, no. Let him talk.

07:17.400 --> 07:20.299
Let him talk. This is a democracy.

07:20.300 --> 07:23.199
Oh, this country, a democracy? Right.

07:23.200 --> 07:25.399
Our family is a democracy.

07:25.400 --> 07:27.399
This country is my family,

07:27.400 --> 07:30.300
and the only way to
truly unite that family

07:30.400 --> 07:31.400
is revolution.

07:31.500 --> 07:32.400
Revolution?

07:33.300 --> 07:34.200
Revolution, yes.

07:34.400 --> 07:36.399
I just can't believe it.

07:36.400 --> 07:39.299
A son of mine that would support

07:39.300 --> 07:41.499
the random violence of revolution?

07:41.500 --> 07:43.400
You better start believing it.

07:43.500 --> 07:46.299
What you need is a little evolution,

07:46.300 --> 07:47.300
not revolution.

07:47.301 --> 07:48.399
Correct.

07:48.400 --> 07:50.399
The poet.

07:50.400 --> 07:52.200
Club owner, poet.

07:52.400 --> 07:54.299
You're lucky you're on the
other side of the room.

07:54.300 --> 07:55.300
I feel lucky,

07:55.301 --> 07:57.300
because it probably stinks
on that side of the room.

07:57.400 --> 07:58.200
Please.

07:58.400 --> 07:59.200
Happy Anniversary.

07:59.400 --> 08:00.400
You are too much.

08:00.401 --> 08:02.199
Did I forget to say that?
Happy Anniversary?

08:02.200 --> 08:03.399
Just watch your mouth.

08:03.400 --> 08:05.499
What? You've been watching
it the whole time.

08:05.500 --> 08:07.400
If I hear one more word of disrespect

08:07.500 --> 08:09.300
coming out of your mouth,

08:09.400 --> 08:11.499
I'm gonna deal with it personally.

08:11.500 --> 08:13.299
Do you understand me?

08:13.300 --> 08:14.200
What?

08:14.400 --> 08:16.199
You understand what I just said to you?

08:16.200 --> 08:17.200
I understand.

08:17.300 --> 08:19.299
You listen to your father
when he's speaking to you,

08:19.300 --> 08:20.400
and you show respect!

08:20.500 --> 08:21.400
Calm down, Fico.

08:21.400 --> 08:22.400
No, you calm down!

08:23.300 --> 08:24.399
Okay. Okay. Okay. Okay.

08:24.400 --> 08:26.399
You want me to come over there?

08:26.400 --> 08:27.400
Okay.

08:27.401 --> 08:29.200
Huh? You want me to come over there?

08:31.200 --> 08:32.200
Stop it!

08:32.201 --> 08:33.400
Come on. Come on.

08:35.400 --> 08:38.200
Stop it! Stop it.

08:38.299 --> 08:40.399
Four against one, huh? Stop it.

08:40.400 --> 08:41.400
Sit down. Sit down.

08:41.400 --> 08:42.400
Is this a democracy?

08:42.400 --> 08:43.400
Sit down.

08:43.400 --> 08:45.399
You got your little show. Sit down.

08:45.400 --> 08:48.399
Sit down, right? How is it? Sit down!

08:48.400 --> 08:50.400
Is this a random act of violence, Papi?

08:51.200 --> 08:52.400
Huh?

08:58.500 --> 08:59.500
They shot Lieutenant Dario.

09:00.300 --> 09:02.300
Did they get good descriptions this time?

09:04.300 --> 09:06.199
Did he mention Peligro again?

09:06.200 --> 09:07.300
Mm-hmm.

09:10.400 --> 09:12.199
What happened?

09:12.200 --> 09:14.300
I'm not gonna have this conversation.

09:14.400 --> 09:16.199
With you, you, you, or any of you.

09:16.200 --> 09:17.300
You know what?

09:17.400 --> 09:19.199
You have no idea What's
going on in this country.

09:19.200 --> 09:21.200
It's sad that you're a
professor and you have zero

09:21.300 --> 09:24.299
zero idea of what is going
on in your own classroom.

09:24.300 --> 09:26.299
Then can you enlighten me?

09:26.300 --> 09:28.299
Can you tell me what's going on?

09:28.300 --> 09:32.400
Discontent, anger... desperation.

09:32.500 --> 09:34.400
That's what's going on in this country,

09:35.300 --> 09:36.200
everywhere in this country,

09:36.300 --> 09:38.199
and especially at your university.

09:38.200 --> 09:40.300
Revolution, okay? Lt happened in
France, it happened in Russia,

09:40.400 --> 09:42.200
and it's happening here,
and it's happening now.

09:42.300 --> 09:44.300
Nobody wants a revolution.

09:44.400 --> 09:45.400
You don't want a revolution.

09:46.200 --> 09:48.200
But like it or not, it's coming.

09:48.300 --> 09:50.400
The people, they want it.

09:50.500 --> 09:52.300
How do you know?

09:52.400 --> 09:55.300
Has the people of Cuba spoken
to you in your chosen ears?

09:55.400 --> 09:58.399
No. Batista must be eliminated.

09:58.400 --> 10:00.200
And then what?

10:00.300 --> 10:02.499
Freedom. Democracy.

10:02.500 --> 10:03.500
Right, yeah.

10:03.500 --> 10:04.500
Power to the people.

10:04.500 --> 10:05.500
That's easier said than done.

10:05.500 --> 10:06.400
It can be done,

10:07.300 --> 10:08.400
but the first thing you have to do

10:09.200 --> 10:10.400
is kill that son of a bitch.

10:10.500 --> 10:11.500
Kill, kill, kill, kill, kill.

10:12.300 --> 10:16.200
Have you ever thought to
live for your country?

10:16.300 --> 10:19.199
Yes. Live. I am living!

10:19.200 --> 10:21.199
I live, and I let die.

10:21.200 --> 10:22.400
Let the tyrant die.

10:23.200 --> 10:24.500
A fish is caught by its mouth.

10:25.300 --> 10:30.199
You need the earth on
your hands, not blood.

10:30.200 --> 10:32.200
Take sanctuary at the farm.

10:32.300 --> 10:35.300
My son doesn't need sanctuary.

10:35.400 --> 10:38.299
He just needs to reform his character,

10:38.300 --> 10:43.200
for a man's character is his destiny.

10:43.300 --> 10:44.300
What book did you get that from?

10:44.500 --> 10:45.500
Maybe you should read a couple.

10:46.300 --> 10:47.200
Where do you stand, Fico?

10:47.300 --> 10:49.500
Where do you stand?

10:50.300 --> 10:51.300
Right here with my family.

10:51.301 --> 10:53.399
I see that. You're just a spectator.

10:53.400 --> 10:55.299
You just watch the parade go by.

10:55.300 --> 10:57.199
Let me tell you something, Fico.

10:57.200 --> 10:59.399
Your days of hiding in this
cork-lined palace are numbered.

10:59.400 --> 11:02.200
Pretty soon, you and you and you

11:02.300 --> 11:04.300
and you are gonna have
to make a decision.

11:04.400 --> 11:06.300
Are you in the parade, or are you not?

11:06.400 --> 11:08.400
I have made my decision.

11:11.300 --> 11:12.200
That means good night!

11:12.300 --> 11:14.200
Good night in Cuban!

11:14.400 --> 11:17.200
Buenas noches!

11:17.300 --> 11:20.200
Buenas noches to you all!

12:00.300 --> 12:02.400
Good evening.

12:03.300 --> 12:04.400
That depends.

12:06.300 --> 12:09.200
It usually does, doesn't it?

12:11.400 --> 12:13.400
It was a great show tonight.

12:17.300 --> 12:18.400
Great show.

12:25.300 --> 12:28.300
Do you know a guy named Peligro?

12:28.400 --> 12:31.299
Who?

12:31.300 --> 12:33.400
Peligro.

12:34.300 --> 12:36.400
Is he a percussionist?

12:44.300 --> 12:47.199
Would you know a guy named Alberto Mora?

12:47.200 --> 12:48.200
Is he a friend of yours?

12:48.400 --> 12:50.300
Someone here to see you.

12:55.400 --> 12:57.400
I had nowhere else to go.

13:00.300 --> 13:01.300
Have you seen him?

13:02.500 --> 13:04.400
All the time.

13:12.500 --> 13:16.200
Next time you see him, say good-bye.

13:24.400 --> 13:25.499
When I get to the pearly gates,

13:25.500 --> 13:28.399
you know what I'm gonna
ask for, don't you?

13:28.400 --> 13:30.399
A bottle of Bacardi? No, a case.

13:30.400 --> 13:32.199
Don't forget the Victrola.

13:32.200 --> 13:33.399
You're not going anywhere
without your dance partner.

13:33.400 --> 13:34.400
Okay, I'll stay.

13:39.400 --> 13:40.500
Viejo. What is he saying?

13:41.200 --> 13:42.400
Uh-oh, the ticking clock.

13:43.200 --> 13:44.400
Fico.

13:51.300 --> 13:55.300
Well, I wanted to say that in our house,

13:55.400 --> 13:57.300
Sunday dinner is not...

13:57.400 --> 13:59.299
A moveable feast.

13:59.300 --> 14:04.300
Uh-huh. All my sons are
welcome, but not...

14:04.400 --> 14:06.199
Not after6.

14:06.200 --> 14:09.399
And it is 6 and 3 minutes, Fico.

14:09.400 --> 14:11.300
I know, but I thought he said after6.

14:13.300 --> 14:16.399
Okay. Okay. Now, um...

14:16.400 --> 14:20.199
I want to make a wish.

14:20.200 --> 14:24.299
If change is going to
come to our country,

14:24.300 --> 14:29.200
I wish that our home remains an island,

14:29.400 --> 14:35.299
and that despite all of our differences,

14:35.300 --> 14:38.300
we always put family first.

14:40.300 --> 14:43.200
And food second.

14:43.400 --> 14:44.400
Salud. Salud.

14:44.401 --> 14:47.300
It's a joke, my brother.
I'm just kidding.

14:57.300 --> 14:59.200
So it's all in the family.

14:59.300 --> 15:00.300
It's all in the family.

15:00.301 --> 15:02.300
I tell you, I swear to God it is.

15:02.400 --> 15:05.399
Hello, Senator. How are you?

15:05.400 --> 15:07.399
I've been better.

15:07.400 --> 15:09.399
I come to see your father.

15:09.400 --> 15:12.299
No one knows more about
constitutional law.

15:12.300 --> 15:14.299
Am I interrupting?

15:14.300 --> 15:16.400
I mean, he's picking for
compliments, Senator.

15:17.300 --> 15:18.300
Okay, I'm gonna give you one.

15:18.400 --> 15:20.399
Do you think the light
interrupts the day?

15:20.400 --> 15:21.400
Sometimes.

15:21.401 --> 15:24.299
We intend to pass a resolution

15:24.300 --> 15:25.400
that will remove Batista

15:26.300 --> 15:29.399
through the constitutional process.

15:29.400 --> 15:31.199
Senator Cossio has asked me

15:31.200 --> 15:33.200
to prepare a speech for him.

15:33.300 --> 15:35.400
This is the opening statement.

15:36.300 --> 15:40.299
Uh, I've made reference to Seneca.

15:40.300 --> 15:41.300
Read it aloud, Senator,

15:41.301 --> 15:44.399
so we can hear how it sounds.

15:44.400 --> 15:47.399
Okay. Please.

15:47.400 --> 15:53.199
Mr. Speaker, I must protest...

15:53.200 --> 15:56.299
as Seneca did in ancient Rome,

15:56.300 --> 15:59.500
of the violence of office.

16:00.300 --> 16:03.399
Today, we, the citizens of Cuba,

16:03.400 --> 16:05.400
are being persecuted by a tyrant

16:06.300 --> 16:07.399
and his reign of terror,

16:07.400 --> 16:11.300
meted out to our
population by his police,

16:11.400 --> 16:15.299
and especially by a certain
colonel in the force.

16:15.300 --> 16:20.299
Whose name has become
synonymous with sudden death.

16:20.300 --> 16:24.299
Seneca was persecuted by two tyrants,

16:24.300 --> 16:27.300
Caligula and Nero.

16:27.400 --> 16:29.200
In spite of that,

16:29.300 --> 16:32.400
Seneca advocated the
return to the Republic...

16:33.200 --> 16:35.399
unafraid.

16:35.400 --> 16:40.400
Mr. Speaker, Seneca, not
the Neros of this world,

16:41.300 --> 16:44.500
should be an example to us.

16:57.200 --> 16:59.399
Fangio, I am your biggest fan.

16:59.400 --> 17:02.199
Get in the car. Just get in the car.

17:02.200 --> 17:03.399
Get in the car. Get in.

17:03.400 --> 17:06.199
What do you want? Money?

17:06.200 --> 17:07.200
Publicity.

17:09.400 --> 17:11.398
Fangio freed, Grand Prix cancelled,

17:11.400 --> 17:13.400
26th of July Movement responsible.

17:14.200 --> 17:15.398
And listen to what Fangio said.

17:15.400 --> 17:16.300
All they wanted from me

17:16.400 --> 17:18.400
is that I help them further their cause.

17:18.500 --> 17:22.300
But I don't know anything
about causes, only cars.

17:22.500 --> 17:24.300
And when they ask him how he was treated,

17:24.500 --> 17:26.400
They were quintessential gentlemen.

17:27.200 --> 17:29.399
Do you think I'm a quintessential
gentleman, Mercedes?

17:29.400 --> 17:31.400
Huh?

17:32.200 --> 17:35.199
What was so funny? What
were you laughing about?

17:35.200 --> 17:37.200
The funnies.

17:37.300 --> 17:38.500
The funnies? That
newspaper has no funnies.

17:40.300 --> 17:42.199
Why don't you try the one
about the kidnappers.

17:42.200 --> 17:43.200
Who only wanted publicity?

17:43.200 --> 17:44.200
Stop it!

17:44.400 --> 17:46.300
That's funny. That's funny.

17:46.400 --> 17:47.400
Leave him alone! Stop!

17:48.300 --> 17:51.299
Yeah. Come on.

17:51.300 --> 17:52.400
Stop! Let him go!

17:56.300 --> 17:57.400
Please stop!

17:58.400 --> 18:01.299
Stop it! Stop it!

18:01.300 --> 18:02.300
Stop it!

18:13.300 --> 18:15.299
Huh?

18:15.300 --> 18:16.499
You want to be tough? Huh?

18:16.500 --> 18:19.299
Wanna play in my city?

18:19.300 --> 18:20.400
Spoiled rich bastard!

18:22.300 --> 18:25.300
You do not want to disappoint me.

18:25.400 --> 18:28.299
Believe me.

18:28.300 --> 18:30.299
I'm gonna go for a walk.

18:30.300 --> 18:33.299
When I get back,

18:33.300 --> 18:35.400
I want you to tell me who Peligro is.

18:43.300 --> 18:44.400
I'm back.

18:46.400 --> 18:49.400
Who's Peligro? Huh?

18:56.200 --> 18:58.300
You're not a good listener.

19:00.200 --> 19:03.200
Whoa, whoa, whoa.

19:16.400 --> 19:20.399
Ooh. No, I'm okay, I'm okay.

19:20.400 --> 19:24.299
I'm gonna go for a walk, okay?

19:24.300 --> 19:26.200
So you better be thinking
about who Peligro is,

19:26.400 --> 19:29.200
'cause you're next.

19:29.300 --> 19:32.200
Let's go for some coffee.

19:32.300 --> 19:35.200
You're here about your brother.

19:35.300 --> 19:37.199
Your little brother's a criminal

19:37.200 --> 19:39.399
a dangerous criminal.

19:39.400 --> 19:41.199
No doubt about that.

19:41.200 --> 19:43.199
I've got his file if you wanna read it.

19:43.200 --> 19:45.200
No, thank you.

19:46.400 --> 19:48.199
I know my brother,

19:48.200 --> 19:51.400
and no file will ever change that.

19:51.500 --> 19:56.199
Fico, we've known each other
since we were in prep school.

19:56.200 --> 19:57.299
I've always been straight with you.

19:57.300 --> 19:58.300
That's true.

19:58.400 --> 20:00.300
Have you ever known me
to change my signals?

20:00.400 --> 20:02.200
Not when you were my catcher.

20:02.300 --> 20:04.300
Fico, you're pitching
for your brother now.

20:04.400 --> 20:06.300
You're pitching wild.

20:06.400 --> 20:08.400
He's guilty. There's no doubt about that.

20:09.300 --> 20:11.400
I know it and you know it.

20:12.300 --> 20:14.200
He's my brother, Braulio.

20:18.400 --> 20:20.200
I need your help.

20:25.200 --> 20:26.200
Okay.

20:27.300 --> 20:28.400
I think you should get out of Havana,

20:29.200 --> 20:30.200
go to New York or Miami,

20:30.201 --> 20:32.199
and I'm gonna take care of the tickets.

20:32.200 --> 20:34.200
Fico, Fidel's gonna take care of me.

20:36.300 --> 20:38.200
I'm leaving for the Sierra Maestra.

20:38.300 --> 20:39.400
Hey.

20:42.300 --> 20:44.200
Fico, I have no choice.

20:47.400 --> 20:49.200
What about your family?

20:49.300 --> 20:52.200
Everything I do is for my family.

20:57.300 --> 20:58.400
I love you.

21:12.200 --> 21:13.400
Uh, come in.

21:15.300 --> 21:16.300
Can I help you?

21:16.301 --> 21:18.299
Al sent me.

21:18.300 --> 21:19.500
Who?

21:21.500 --> 21:23.200
Al.

21:23.300 --> 21:24.499
He's a friend of yours, isn't he?

21:24.500 --> 21:26.300
Are you auditioning?

21:27.300 --> 21:29.299
Yes, I am.

21:29.300 --> 21:30.400
What's your line?

21:30.500 --> 21:31.400
I'm a comedian.

21:33.400 --> 21:36.299
I'm a stand-up comedian.

21:36.300 --> 21:39.200
Who prefers to remain seated.

21:39.300 --> 21:40.399
That's it? That's your line?

21:40.400 --> 21:42.200
Yeah.

21:43.400 --> 21:44.400
Some jokes for your emcee.

21:45.200 --> 21:46.200
He writes his own jokes.

21:46.300 --> 21:48.300
They're lousy. So are yours.

21:48.400 --> 21:50.299
Touch?

21:50.300 --> 21:52.399
You want some help writing
some of your other material?

21:52.400 --> 21:55.199
Nobody writes anybody's
material around here.

21:55.200 --> 21:56.299
You just improvise?

21:56.300 --> 21:58.199
You can call it that. Try New York.

21:58.200 --> 22:01.199
Too cold. Too rich.

22:01.200 --> 22:02.300
Too close to home.

22:02.400 --> 22:04.299
Well, I'm afraid you're going to have to

22:04.300 --> 22:05.300
find another line of work, then.

22:06.200 --> 22:07.299
I can't.

22:07.300 --> 22:10.199
The laughter you just
become addicted to it.

22:10.200 --> 22:12.199
What'd you say your name was?

22:12.200 --> 22:16.400
I didn't. I said Al sent me.

22:16.500 --> 22:20.400
If you know Al, you know me.

22:21.300 --> 22:23.300
Oh, Al's friend.

22:23.500 --> 22:24.400
Where've you been?

22:24.500 --> 22:26.299
Where haven't I been?

22:26.300 --> 22:28.300
Federico, remember your appointment.

22:28.500 --> 22:30.300
And don't forget your dancing shoes.

22:30.400 --> 22:31.400
You're going to need them.

22:32.300 --> 22:35.299
Oh, Rodney?

22:35.300 --> 22:36.400
Maestro?

22:37.300 --> 22:40.300
Oh, nevermind.

22:42.400 --> 22:46.299
I think I have a job for you after all.

22:46.300 --> 22:48.400
Finally, after all these years

22:48.500 --> 22:51.400
of sacrifice and dedication,

22:51.500 --> 22:54.300
a break.

23:00.300 --> 23:02.299
Why can't you tell me who we're meeting?

23:02.300 --> 23:03.300
It's better that way.

23:03.300 --> 23:04.300
I love surprises.

23:04.400 --> 23:05.400
Just don't say a word

23:06.200 --> 23:07.200
no matter what.

23:07.201 --> 23:09.399
Sit there, pretend you're my security.
That's it.

23:09.400 --> 23:11.400
Howâ€™s this? Cozy enough?

23:12.200 --> 23:13.399
Look a little bit more dangerous.

23:13.400 --> 23:15.300
How about this?

23:17.400 --> 23:18.200
More dangerous.

23:19.400 --> 23:21.400
This is my meanest.

23:24.400 --> 23:26.200
Save that.

23:27.300 --> 23:28.200
Can I make a wish?

23:28.300 --> 23:29.300
Be my guest.

23:29.500 --> 23:34.399
I wish for a tall, athletic,
caramel-colored beauty.

23:34.400 --> 23:35.400
Okay.

23:39.300 --> 23:41.400
An open-door policy is the
sign of a great host.

23:42.300 --> 23:44.200
Mr. Lansky, come in. Welcome.

23:44.400 --> 23:47.299
Should I call you Federico,

23:47.300 --> 23:50.200
Mr. Fellove, or Fico?

23:52.400 --> 23:56.200
Depends on whether you
shake my hand or not.

23:56.300 --> 23:57.399
Call me Fico.

23:57.400 --> 23:59.400
You can call my Meyer. All my friends do.

24:00.300 --> 24:02.300
Have a seat.

24:03.400 --> 24:04.400
Who is this guy?

24:04.401 --> 24:07.399
Don't mind him, he's just a comedian.

24:07.400 --> 24:08.400
A blind one?

24:08.400 --> 24:09.400
Mute.

24:09.401 --> 24:11.199
That's funny.

24:11.200 --> 24:12.300
Would you like a drink?

24:12.400 --> 24:16.399
A little seltzer, unless
you happen to, uh...

24:16.400 --> 24:17.400
have an egg cream.

24:18.200 --> 24:19.200
I have eggs and I have cream.

24:19.400 --> 24:20.400
And you have a blind comedian.

24:20.500 --> 24:22.300
Mute.

24:24.500 --> 24:26.300
An egg cream is neither egg nor cream.

24:26.400 --> 24:28.300
Would you like to know how to make one?

24:28.500 --> 24:29.500
Well, that would've
been my next question.

24:30.200 --> 24:31.400
Well, let's see how this goes first.

24:32.200 --> 24:35.200
A little seltzer for now.
Cuts the humidity.

24:38.400 --> 24:40.500
You hear that, comedian?

24:41.200 --> 24:42.400
You said something on the phone
about a business opportunity.

24:43.200 --> 24:46.200
Well played. Le Chaim.

24:48.400 --> 24:51.199
I propose a partnership between us.

24:51.200 --> 24:54.199
20% goes to the house,

24:54.200 --> 24:56.299
the rest to me, my associates.

24:56.300 --> 24:57.300
It doesn't have to be anything big.

24:58.200 --> 24:59.399
I mean, this is very cozy here.

24:59.400 --> 25:01.199
You could have a couple of tables,

25:01.200 --> 25:04.399
craps, you know,
blackjack, a wheel or two.

25:04.400 --> 25:06.200
This is nice.

25:06.300 --> 25:08.200
Mr. Lansky.

25:10.200 --> 25:12.400
Call him Meyer.

25:13.300 --> 25:14.400
Or Mr. Lansky.

25:15.200 --> 25:16.400
You want him here?

25:17.300 --> 25:19.399
Meyer, I appreciate the offer,

25:19.400 --> 25:21.300
but, regretfully, I have to pass.

25:21.400 --> 25:24.299
Now, I know this is a
tremendous opportunity for me.

25:24.300 --> 25:27.399
However, El Tropico is a place of music,

25:27.400 --> 25:29.400
and that's how I would like it to stay.

25:33.200 --> 25:34.399
Let me rephrase.

25:34.400 --> 25:36.200
We have the beginning

25:36.300 --> 25:38.200
of a mutually beneficial relationship.

25:38.300 --> 25:40.399
It would be a pity to see it
end before it even began.

25:40.400 --> 25:41.400
Yes, it would.

25:41.401 --> 25:43.400
All right.

25:47.400 --> 25:51.300
I was informed you were a reasonable man.

25:51.400 --> 25:53.299
I hope I wasn't misinformed.

25:53.300 --> 25:54.200
You weren't.

25:54.400 --> 25:56.399
What I can offer you in return

25:56.400 --> 25:58.399
is what I offer all my friends

25:58.400 --> 26:00.400
an open-door policy.

26:01.300 --> 26:03.300
Consider my club your home any time.

26:03.500 --> 26:05.399
What, free seltzer?

26:05.400 --> 26:08.199
As much as you want.

26:08.200 --> 26:10.200
You know, in my business, Mr. Fellove,

26:10.400 --> 26:12.400
We have friends and we have enemies,

26:13.300 --> 26:15.300
but we don't have acquaintances.

26:17.200 --> 26:20.300
I hope to hear some good news very soon.

26:30.200 --> 26:34.299
Is that Meyer Lansky... Meyer Lansky?

26:34.300 --> 26:36.299
The head of the mob.

26:36.300 --> 26:38.200
I resign.

27:00.200 --> 27:03.199
Are you wearing false eyelashes,
or are you truly bashful?

27:03.200 --> 27:04.399
I never wear false eyelashes.

27:04.400 --> 27:05.300
That's my girl.

27:06.500 --> 27:07.400
Am I?

27:30.300 --> 27:31.399
Whose idea was that?

27:31.400 --> 27:33.400
Rodney's.

27:36.300 --> 27:37.399
Are you gonna be watching?

27:37.400 --> 27:40.300
Always.

28:12.300 --> 28:14.300
What's the matter?

28:19.300 --> 28:20.300
What's wrong?

28:20.301 --> 28:22.400
Luis has another woman.

28:22.500 --> 28:24.200
Another woman?

28:28.300 --> 28:32.199
He hasn't come home in two days,

28:32.200 --> 28:36.300
and before that, we haven't.

28:36.400 --> 28:38.500
His mind is elsewhere.

28:40.400 --> 28:42.200
Has he called?

28:42.400 --> 28:44.299
Just to say that he's okay,

28:44.300 --> 28:46.500
and that's all he says.

28:48.300 --> 28:51.200
Fico, help me.

28:51.300 --> 28:54.300
You're the only one I can turn to.

28:54.400 --> 28:56.300
I'm gonna take care of it.

29:22.200 --> 29:24.400
She's worried about you.

29:28.200 --> 29:29.400
She came to you?

29:33.200 --> 29:34.400
She's always had a...

29:36.400 --> 29:39.299
very special place in her heart for you.

29:39.300 --> 29:41.399
And you for her.

29:41.400 --> 29:44.399
What's the matter? Talk to me.

29:44.400 --> 29:47.299
I'm not gonna get you involved.

29:47.300 --> 29:50.399
I'm your brother. I'm involved.
What's up?

29:50.400 --> 29:52.299
Is it another woman?

29:52.300 --> 29:53.200
Yes.

29:55.400 --> 29:58.200
Liberty.

30:21.300 --> 30:23.299
You involved with Fidel? No.

30:23.300 --> 30:25.299
26th of July Movement, like Ricardo?

30:25.300 --> 30:26.200
No.

30:28.200 --> 30:31.399
Directorio Revolucionario.

30:31.400 --> 30:33.300
We're no longer associated.

30:33.400 --> 30:36.400
We have our own ideas for Cuba.

30:37.200 --> 30:39.300
Pluralism,

30:39.400 --> 30:41.300
the restoration of the 1940 Constitution.

30:42.200 --> 30:43.200
You know, democracy.

30:43.201 --> 30:44.399
That's what Fidel says he wants.

30:44.400 --> 30:47.300
Sure, that's what he says,
but he can't be trusted.

30:47.400 --> 30:50.300
You think he's a Communist?

30:50.400 --> 30:51.500
A Fidelista.

30:58.300 --> 31:00.400
You have to promise me something.

31:00.500 --> 31:01.400
What?

31:04.400 --> 31:06.300
Anything happens to me...

31:09.400 --> 31:10.500
you'll look after Aurora.

31:13.300 --> 31:15.200
She'll need you.

31:15.300 --> 31:16.400
Here, promise me.

31:19.200 --> 31:21.200
Promise me, Fico.

31:22.400 --> 31:25.299
I need this from you.

31:25.300 --> 31:27.400
I promise you.

31:28.200 --> 31:29.200
But you're gonna promise me

31:29.201 --> 31:32.300
that nothing's gonna
happen to you, right?

31:32.400 --> 31:34.399
Right?

31:34.400 --> 31:38.200
There's no happiness
outside the revolution.

31:47.500 --> 31:49.500
Okay.

31:54.300 --> 31:57.199
Don't do something stupid.

31:57.200 --> 31:59.200
Okay?

32:33.300 --> 32:36.499
Ricardo Fellove, 26th of July Movement.

32:36.500 --> 32:40.299
Fellove. Are you the dancer?

32:40.300 --> 32:43.400
Because we don't need any dancers.

32:46.400 --> 32:49.400
Okay, get off the horse. We're hungry.

33:08.200 --> 33:09.300
It's not another woman.

33:09.400 --> 33:12.300
Then why won't he come back?

33:12.400 --> 33:13.400
He doesn't want us involved.

33:14.300 --> 33:16.299
What is it? The revolution?

33:16.300 --> 33:17.400
He doesn't want us involved.

33:18.300 --> 33:19.300
That's it?

33:19.301 --> 33:20.400
That's it.

33:30.300 --> 33:34.200
Am I supposed to take
that home and be happy?

33:34.300 --> 33:36.200
I'm his wife.

33:36.400 --> 33:38.399
I have the right to be involved.

33:38.400 --> 33:42.199
If something happens to
him, it happens to me.

33:42.200 --> 33:43.399
To all of us.

33:43.400 --> 33:45.500
And then what?

34:33.400 --> 34:37.199
I think it was the Mafia, Meyer Lansky,

34:39.199 --> 34:40.300
but I can't be certain.

34:40.400 --> 34:44.299
Havana is no longer a capital city,

34:44.300 --> 34:48.199
but a capital sin.

34:49.500 --> 34:51.300
This is not new, of course,

34:51.500 --> 34:56.400
but even Jesus had to
whip the moneylenders

34:56.500 --> 34:58.299
out of the temple.

34:58.300 --> 35:03.199
We're badly in need of a

35:03.200 --> 35:05.300
of a Christ with a whip.

35:09.500 --> 35:12.300
I don't know what to do.

35:18.300 --> 35:22.199
Satyagraha.

35:22.200 --> 35:23.299
Do you know what that is?

35:23.300 --> 35:26.199
No.

35:26.200 --> 35:28.300
It is the Hindu word.

35:28.400 --> 35:32.299
For passive resistance.

35:32.300 --> 35:37.200
Gandhi resisted passively,

35:37.300 --> 35:38.200
and he won.

35:41.400 --> 35:44.400
My son, in the sea,

35:44.500 --> 35:46.500
even a shark can drown.

36:19.300 --> 36:21.299
Okay, we all know how to make it

36:21.300 --> 36:23.299
into the Presidential
Palace by heart now?

36:23.300 --> 36:25.200
So let's review one last time.

36:25.300 --> 36:27.500
I will take over the CNQ radio
station and read our statement.

36:28.300 --> 36:29.300
Carbo?

36:29.500 --> 36:32.200
Machado and I will attack with
Peligro through the main gates,

36:32.400 --> 36:34.399
along with Menoyo and his group.

36:34.400 --> 36:36.400
Ignacio, you will provide
sniper protection

36:37.200 --> 36:38.200
and reinforcements.

36:38.300 --> 36:40.400
Any questions?

36:43.200 --> 36:45.300
What do you think, Peligro?

36:53.400 --> 36:55.200
It's time.

37:56.200 --> 37:58.200
Mockingbird Pet Shop. Can I help you?

37:58.300 --> 38:00.400
The bird is in the cage.

38:04.500 --> 38:06.400
He's in.

38:10.200 --> 38:11.300
Long live a free Cuba.

38:11.400 --> 38:13.300
Long live a free Cuba.

38:19.300 --> 38:20.500
Mr. President?

38:24.300 --> 38:26.300
Mr. President?

38:27.400 --> 38:30.300
What is it, Pizzi?

38:30.400 --> 38:34.200
There are urgent matters
for you to attend to.

38:39.200 --> 38:42.200
I've been signing edicts all week,

38:42.300 --> 38:45.299
and you know what I've
been thinking, Pizzi?

38:45.300 --> 38:47.299
I'm a fortunate man

38:47.300 --> 38:51.200
for having had to sign one
single death warrant.

38:51.300 --> 38:54.299
Mr. President, if I might say so myself,

38:54.300 --> 38:58.300
you are a fortunate man,
but also a noble man.

38:58.400 --> 39:00.300
Thank you, Pizzi. That's
very kind of you.

39:01.200 --> 39:03.199
No, no, no, no, no. It is not kindness.

39:03.200 --> 39:05.300
It is historical justice.

39:16.400 --> 39:20.299
Have I ever told you how
much I appreciate you?

39:20.300 --> 39:23.399
No, sir.

39:23.400 --> 39:25.400
Oh.

39:35.300 --> 39:36.300
Sorry I'm late.

39:36.301 --> 39:37.400
I got stuck in Pinelarillo.

39:39.300 --> 39:40.200
What do you want?

39:40.300 --> 39:41.400
I got 450 napkins and tablecloths.

39:41.500 --> 39:44.299
I'm gonna need help
getting it out of here.

39:44.300 --> 39:46.299
I don't have any deliveries
on my list today.

39:46.300 --> 39:47.300
This is the front gate, right?

39:47.301 --> 39:49.200
Yeah, it's the front gate.

39:49.300 --> 39:51.300
They told me 3:00 at the front gate.

39:51.400 --> 39:53.300
Can you check? Can you.

39:53.400 --> 39:55.200
All right. Stay there.

39:57.300 --> 39:58.300
Is any deliveries on the list today?

39:59.200 --> 40:00.200
No.

40:16.400 --> 40:19.200
Let's go! Let's go! Let's go! Let's go!

40:19.300 --> 40:20.200
Go ahead, go in!

40:20.300 --> 40:21.300
Here!

40:25.400 --> 40:27.400
What's that noise?

40:42.500 --> 40:43.400
Come with me! Now!

41:50.200 --> 41:51.200
Let's go!

42:11.200 --> 42:13.300
Fico! The palace is being attacked.

42:13.400 --> 42:16.400
Listen. Manzanita's taken
over the radio station.

42:20.300 --> 42:23.399
People of Cuba, the
dictator Fulgencio Batista

42:23.400 --> 42:26.200
has just met revolutionary justice.

42:27.200 --> 42:28.200
The gunfire that extinguished

42:28.201 --> 42:29.400
the bloody life of the dictator

42:30.200 --> 42:32.200
can still be heard around
the Presidential Palace.

42:33.200 --> 42:35.199
It is we, The Directorio Revolucionario,

42:35.200 --> 42:37.300
the iron hand of the Cuban Revolution.

42:37.400 --> 42:38.400
Who have accomplished the final blow

42:38.500 --> 42:39.400
against this shameful regime

42:39.500 --> 42:41.300
still twisting in its own agony.

42:41.400 --> 42:44.200
Cubans who can hear me, he
has just been eliminated.

42:44.400 --> 42:46.300
Long live a free Cuba!

42:46.400 --> 42:48.300
Que vive una Cuba libre!

43:11.200 --> 43:12.400
Carbo! Carbo!

43:15.400 --> 43:17.300
Luis! Luis!

43:17.400 --> 43:18.300
Luis!

43:20.200 --> 43:21.200
Luis!

43:25.200 --> 43:26.400
Luis!

43:34.300 --> 43:37.500
Pizzi, leave us alone.

43:41.500 --> 43:45.199
With friends or without friends?

43:45.200 --> 43:47.300
As you like.

43:56.200 --> 43:58.200
Pizzi.

43:58.400 --> 43:59.300
Yes, sir?

44:07.400 --> 44:10.299
People of Cuba,

44:10.300 --> 44:14.400
today alien forces made
an attempt on my life.

44:18.300 --> 44:20.199
As you can see,

44:20.200 --> 44:24.399
the news of my demise
is vastly exaggerated.

44:24.400 --> 44:29.300
The President now declares
business as usual in Havana.

44:31.300 --> 44:35.400
I lend a helping hand to
those law-abiding citizens

44:36.200 --> 44:38.400
and our loyal oppositions.

44:40.200 --> 44:45.200
The future of Cuba is safe.

44:45.300 --> 44:47.400
Abuelo!

44:50.300 --> 44:54.300
Our children are safe.

44:58.300 --> 45:00.300
That is all.

45:00.400 --> 45:02.400
Salud.

45:12.500 --> 45:14.299
Life is becoming a dress rehearsal

45:14.300 --> 45:15.500
for a show nobody'll see.

45:21.300 --> 45:22.300
What's the word on Luis?

45:22.301 --> 45:23.399
He's nowhere to be found.

45:23.400 --> 45:24.400
Are you sure he's alive?

45:25.200 --> 45:27.199
Positive.

45:27.200 --> 45:29.199
He might be abroad.

45:29.200 --> 45:30.300
He might be abroad.

45:32.300 --> 45:33.300
I'm leaving.

45:34.500 --> 45:36.300
I'm leaving.

45:44.500 --> 45:46.300
I'm sorry. There's no news.

45:47.300 --> 45:48.300
Was he part of the attack?

45:48.500 --> 45:49.300
Yes.

45:50.500 --> 45:52.399
Why won't you tell me where he is?

45:52.400 --> 45:54.200
Because I don't know where he is.

45:56.200 --> 45:57.499
Fico, if something happens,

45:57.500 --> 45:59.400
I want to be there...

45:59.500 --> 46:00.400
for him.

46:00.500 --> 46:01.400
So do I.

49:20.200 --> 49:22.299
May I offer a serious thought

49:22.300 --> 49:24.300
from someone who's never serious?

49:25.300 --> 49:26.400
No.

49:27.500 --> 49:28.400
Well, that was it.

49:56.200 --> 49:57.399
Mmm.

49:57.400 --> 49:58.400
It's good.

50:02.400 --> 50:05.200
A man with a purpose.

50:28.500 --> 50:30.400
A man with less of a purpose.

50:32.300 --> 50:35.299
Fellove, come on. Please join me.

50:35.300 --> 50:38.400
Mmm. Mmm!

50:45.300 --> 50:47.299
In our house,

50:47.300 --> 50:49.300
Sunday dinner is not a moveable feast.

50:54.300 --> 50:56.300
It is at 6, as usual.

50:57.500 --> 50:59.300
Sorry.

51:01.200 --> 51:03.399
All my sons are welcome, but..

51:03.400 --> 51:05.200
Not a minute after6.

51:08.400 --> 51:12.300
You must always chew. It's
good for your health.

51:12.400 --> 51:14.200
You chew and you chew.

51:15.200 --> 51:16.300
Mmm.

51:16.400 --> 51:18.300
And then you chew some more.

51:22.300 --> 51:26.299
See, I'm a man of... good digestion.

51:26.300 --> 51:31.399
In fact, if I wasn't such a modest man,

51:31.400 --> 51:33.400
I'd say I'm a man of great digestion.

51:35.500 --> 51:38.300
That's why I'm still alive.

51:38.400 --> 51:40.200
About our little business...

51:44.300 --> 51:45.300
our business?

51:45.500 --> 51:47.399
Yeah, our business.

51:47.400 --> 51:49.300
My business is El Tropico.

51:49.400 --> 51:52.300
And I would love to continue
going to El Tropico.

51:56.400 --> 52:01.200
So unless that's a prop for
one of your new shows...

