All right, girls, lose the rifles.

01:21:15.400 --> 01:21:18.200
Very, very unmilitary now.

01:21:18.400 --> 01:21:19.200
M? Sica.

01:21:19.400 --> 01:21:20.400
1, 2, 3.

01:21:24.400 --> 01:21:26.300
Stop the music!

01:21:26.500 --> 01:21:28.300
Stop that music!

01:21:30.400 --> 01:21:31.400
Who are you?

01:21:31.401 --> 01:21:33.400
I am Zoraida Munoz,

01:21:33.500 --> 01:21:35.300
a delegate for the musicians' union.

01:21:35.400 --> 01:21:37.300
What authority do you have
to stop my rehearsal?

01:21:37.400 --> 01:21:40.399
The government gave me the authority.

01:21:40.400 --> 01:21:42.399
See, you own this beautiful cabaret,

01:21:42.400 --> 01:21:43.400
but we own the orchestra.

01:21:44.200 --> 01:21:45.300
Really?

01:21:45.400 --> 01:21:48.200
Really. If I tell the
orchestra not to play,

01:21:48.300 --> 01:21:49.399
they can't play.

01:21:49.400 --> 01:21:51.299
Is that so?

01:21:51.300 --> 01:21:53.399
Fico, we're in the union.

01:21:53.400 --> 01:21:54.400
They control the union.

01:21:56.200 --> 01:21:58.299
I see. And under what grounds do you have

01:21:58.300 --> 01:22:00.499
to come here and stop my show?

01:22:00.500 --> 01:22:02.299
You just can't use the saxophone

01:22:02.300 --> 01:22:03.400
in the orchestra anymore.

01:22:03.500 --> 01:22:05.200
Come again?

01:22:05.300 --> 01:22:07.499
The saxophone is a instrument
of the imperialists.

01:22:07.500 --> 01:22:10.400
The saxophone was invented

01:22:10.500 --> 01:22:13.299
by a man named Sax in Belgium!

01:22:13.300 --> 01:22:17.299
Do you know what the Belgian imperialists

01:22:17.300 --> 01:22:18.400
are doing in the Congo?

01:22:18.500 --> 01:22:20.299
They're a bunch of murderers.

01:22:20.300 --> 01:22:21.300
You don't say.

01:22:21.301 --> 01:22:22.400
No, I do say!

01:22:22.500 --> 01:22:24.299
And I am saying

01:22:24.300 --> 01:22:26.300
that if you want the orchestra to play,

01:22:26.500 --> 01:22:28.400
then you have to go
without the saxophone.

01:22:29.300 --> 01:22:31.300
Otherwise, I will stop the show.

01:22:56.300 --> 01:22:57.200
Great show.

01:22:57.400 --> 01:22:59.199
What's wrong with it?

01:22:59.200 --> 01:23:00.200
What's wrong with it?

01:23:00.201 --> 01:23:01.299
You mean besides the fact

01:23:01.300 --> 01:23:03.299
that they executed my friend in
two days without due process?

01:23:03.300 --> 01:23:05.400
And now they're threatening
to close down my club

01:23:05.500 --> 01:23:08.399
because we can't use
saxophones in the orchestra.

01:23:08.400 --> 01:23:10.500
Saxophones!

01:23:12.300 --> 01:23:14.200
Besides that?

01:23:16.200 --> 01:23:18.200
What about the pigeons?

01:23:18.300 --> 01:23:19.300
The pigeon.

01:23:19.301 --> 01:23:21.300
Never work with pigeons.

01:23:22.200 --> 01:23:23.299
Guano.

01:23:23.300 --> 01:23:25.299
Well, at least we don't have to deal

01:23:25.300 --> 01:23:27.399
with the likes of Meyer Lansky anymore.

01:23:27.400 --> 01:23:28.400
Maybe worse.

01:23:29.200 --> 01:23:31.400
Here's to a Cuba libre.

01:23:31.500 --> 01:23:34.300
Well, what do we do now?

01:23:35.300 --> 01:23:37.200
Let's go to Hernando's.

01:23:37.300 --> 01:23:39.400
Hernando's Hideaway.

01:23:40.200 --> 01:23:41.400
Now, that has a certain ring to it.

01:23:44.400 --> 01:23:45.400
I'm going.

01:23:45.401 --> 01:23:47.299
I'm going,

01:23:47.300 --> 01:23:51.200
which translates to I'm not going.

01:24:22.500 --> 01:24:24.400
Dance with me.

01:25:59.300 --> 01:26:00.400
What's wrong?

01:26:06.400 --> 01:26:07.400
What's happening?

01:26:08.200 --> 01:26:09.200
Viva El suerte de Fidel.

01:26:13.400 --> 01:26:15.200
Viva Fidel!

01:26:17.400 --> 01:26:19.399
It's Fidel.

01:26:19.400 --> 01:26:23.199
The guy we saw performing
with a pigeon once.

01:26:23.200 --> 01:26:25.300
Let's go over. I want to meet him.

01:26:26.200 --> 01:26:27.300
Too early in the day for that.

01:26:27.500 --> 01:26:29.299
There are some things I need to say.

01:26:29.300 --> 01:26:30.400
I want to speak with him.

01:26:31.300 --> 01:26:33.299
Will you please take me?

01:26:33.300 --> 01:26:34.300
What?

01:26:34.400 --> 01:26:36.399
There are some things I need to say.

01:26:36.400 --> 01:26:37.400
Would you please take me?

01:26:39.300 --> 01:26:40.400
No.

01:26:41.200 --> 01:26:42.400
I'll go on my own, then.

01:27:12.500 --> 01:27:15.199
Fidel's inviting us to
have breakfast with him.

01:27:15.200 --> 01:27:16.400
He invited you, not me.

01:27:16.500 --> 01:27:19.200
I don't think it's proper
for me to turn him down.

01:27:19.400 --> 01:27:22.200
Well, I don't think it's
proper for me to wait around.

01:27:25.300 --> 01:27:26.300
You're jealous.

01:27:26.301 --> 01:27:29.300
Of a circus ringmaster?

01:27:29.400 --> 01:27:30.400
You don't know me.

01:27:30.401 --> 01:27:32.400
I thought you never paid?

01:27:32.500 --> 01:27:35.400
I always pay sooner or later.

01:28:10.200 --> 01:28:10.500
Cecilia?

01:28:10.501 --> 01:28:12.400
Yes, dear.

01:28:13.200 --> 01:28:15.199
Was that Ricardo at the door?

01:28:15.200 --> 01:28:17.400
No, no. They had the wrong house.

01:28:18.200 --> 01:28:19.300
Oh.

01:28:33.400 --> 01:28:35.199
Aurora.

01:28:35.200 --> 01:28:36.300
Or should I say companera?

01:28:37.200 --> 01:28:40.199
Fidel sends his regard and admiration.

01:28:40.200 --> 01:28:42.199
He regrets that he couldn't be here

01:28:42.200 --> 01:28:43.300
to greet you personally.

01:28:43.400 --> 01:28:45.199
He sent me in his place

01:28:45.200 --> 01:28:47.300
to offer you something
of great importance.

01:28:48.200 --> 01:28:49.299
Good news and bad news.

01:28:49.300 --> 01:28:51.199
Somebody I know?

01:28:51.200 --> 01:28:52.500
Somebody you don't know.

01:28:53.200 --> 01:28:55.200
Aurora Bernal de Fellove,

01:28:55.300 --> 01:28:57.200
a widow of a martyr of the revolution

01:28:57.300 --> 01:28:58.300
Luis Fellove, who was killed

01:28:58.400 --> 01:29:01.299
in the massacre on Humboldt Street.

01:29:01.300 --> 01:29:03.300
After his heroic exploits

01:29:03.500 --> 01:29:06.300
during the assault on the
Presidential Palace.

01:29:06.500 --> 01:29:09.400
Comrade Aurora has been named.

01:29:09.500 --> 01:29:11.400
widow of the Revolution of the Year.

01:29:12.300 --> 01:29:14.299
Nice writers they have down here, huh?

01:29:14.300 --> 01:29:15.400
widow of the Revolution.

01:29:15.500 --> 01:29:17.299
Does that mean

01:29:17.300 --> 01:29:19.299
she was formerly married
to the revolution,

01:29:19.300 --> 01:29:22.399
and now the aforementioned
revolution is dead?

01:29:22.400 --> 01:29:25.199
And did that happen this year, too?

01:29:25.200 --> 01:29:26.400
And the copy

01:29:27.200 --> 01:29:29.399
even I can write better than that.

01:29:29.400 --> 01:29:31.400
But...

01:29:32.300 --> 01:29:34.399
it does suggest...

01:29:34.400 --> 01:29:36.399
heads up now.

01:29:36.400 --> 01:29:39.399
The Merry widow of the Revolution

01:29:39.400 --> 01:29:42.400
some songs, a little bit of business.

01:29:43.200 --> 01:29:44.399
Very nice musical you could open

01:29:44.400 --> 01:29:46.300
right here in Fico's Palace.

01:29:48.200 --> 01:29:49.500
I'd like to run with this one if I could.

01:29:50.300 --> 01:29:52.399
I'm gonna go see if I ca

01:29:52.400 --> 01:29:53.400
n nail down the rights.

01:29:58.500 --> 01:29:59.400
Hello.

01:29:59.500 --> 01:30:01.200
Hello, Fico.

01:30:01.300 --> 01:30:03.300
You haven't called me.

01:30:03.400 --> 01:30:05.400
I had work to do.

01:30:06.300 --> 01:30:07.200
You've just disappeared.

01:30:07.300 --> 01:30:09.200
I missed you.

01:30:09.300 --> 01:30:11.400
Work to do.

01:30:11.500 --> 01:30:13.400
Have you seen it in the papers?

01:30:13.500 --> 01:30:15.400
Isn't it wonderful?

01:30:17.400 --> 01:30:19.300
Yes, I'm glad to hear it.

01:30:19.400 --> 01:30:21.300
Luis should be so proud.

01:30:21.500 --> 01:30:22.500
Right.

01:30:23.300 --> 01:30:25.299
The reason I called you is to invite you

01:30:25.300 --> 01:30:27.400
to a little celebration in my honor.

01:30:28.300 --> 01:30:29.400
Would you please come?

01:30:30.200 --> 01:30:32.200
Maybe some other time.
Listen, I have to go.

01:30:32.300 --> 01:30:33.300
All right.

01:30:33.400 --> 01:30:35.399
Please call me.

01:30:35.400 --> 01:30:37.400
I love you.

01:30:48.300 --> 01:30:50.300
Once more into the breach.

01:30:54.400 --> 01:30:55.300
What can I do for you?

01:30:55.400 --> 01:30:57.299
We're closing down this cabaret

01:30:57.300 --> 01:30:59.299
on account of gambling.

01:30:59.300 --> 01:31:00.300
Gambling.

01:31:00.500 --> 01:31:02.300
Illegal gambling.

01:31:02.400 --> 01:31:03.200
What illegal gambling?

01:31:03.400 --> 01:31:06.500
We caught two stagehands playing cards.

01:31:07.300 --> 01:31:08.200
And that's illegal.

01:31:08.300 --> 01:31:10.199
Oh, it's worse than that.

01:31:10.200 --> 01:31:12.200
It is a dangerous
distraction to the masses.

01:31:12.300 --> 01:31:15.300
The opium of the people, Marx said.

01:31:15.500 --> 01:31:18.500
I thought Marx said religion
was the opiate of the people.

01:31:19.300 --> 01:31:20.300
Marx said that, too.

01:31:20.400 --> 01:31:22.200
Karl or Groucho?

01:31:23.300 --> 01:31:26.299
Also an illegal gambling game.

01:31:26.300 --> 01:31:27.300
The revolutionary government

01:31:27.301 --> 01:31:29.300
will decide when, how,

01:31:29.400 --> 01:31:34.300
and if this premises will
be functioning again.

01:31:36.400 --> 01:31:39.400
You son of a bitch! How dare you?

01:31:42.400 --> 01:31:44.200
I'm an artist!

01:31:44.300 --> 01:31:46.300
Puta! Cono!

01:31:46.400 --> 01:31:48.400
Likewise.

01:33:04.300 --> 01:33:07.400
Hello! My nephew the hero!

01:33:09.300 --> 01:33:11.200
Good to see you.

01:33:11.300 --> 01:33:12.400
My goodness.

01:33:22.300 --> 01:33:24.400
There's nothing like an old Victrola.

01:33:25.300 --> 01:33:29.200
Mmm-mmm-mmm.

01:33:29.300 --> 01:33:31.399
I was just about to make my rounds.

01:33:31.400 --> 01:33:35.200
But first we have a drink, huh?

01:33:36.300 --> 01:33:40.499
And then we'll have a walk,

01:33:40.500 --> 01:33:43.500
talk, a smoke,

01:33:44.300 --> 01:33:45.400
and then...

01:33:47.300 --> 01:33:50.200
...we will eat, huh?

01:33:50.300 --> 01:33:52.300
Ricardito.

01:33:54.200 --> 01:33:55.399
Isn't this beautiful?

01:33:55.400 --> 01:34:00.199
It's a little behind, yes,

01:34:00.200 --> 01:34:04.200
but it shows great promise.

01:34:04.300 --> 01:34:07.300
The day I die...

01:34:07.400 --> 01:34:10.200
all of this will be yours.

01:34:10.300 --> 01:34:12.199
No, it won't.

01:34:12.200 --> 01:34:15.200
Yes, it will, but after I die.

01:34:15.400 --> 01:34:16.300
Ha ha.

01:34:16.400 --> 01:34:19.199
You don't understand. It
belongs to the revolution.

01:34:19.200 --> 01:34:22.200
The revolution will pass, believe me.

01:34:24.300 --> 01:34:28.299
I've seen it all before.

01:34:28.300 --> 01:34:32.300
Menocal, Machado, Batista...

01:34:33.200 --> 01:34:35.300
Where are they now?

01:34:38.400 --> 01:34:39.400
Gone.

01:34:42.300 --> 01:34:44.399
Fidel Castro will pass, too.

01:34:44.400 --> 01:34:49.200
But the land...

01:34:49.300 --> 01:34:52.400
the land, it will endure.

01:34:52.500 --> 01:34:55.400
Fidel Castro sent me personally

01:34:55.500 --> 01:34:57.299
to take vacant possession of this land.

01:34:57.300 --> 01:34:58.300
What are you talking about?

01:34:58.400 --> 01:34:59.400
I'm here too evict you.

01:34:59.500 --> 01:35:03.199
Would you repeat that to me, please?

01:35:03.200 --> 01:35:04.299
This farm is now property of the state.

01:35:04.300 --> 01:35:05.400
I am here to legally inform you

01:35:06.300 --> 01:35:07.300
that you must leave immediately.

01:35:07.400 --> 01:35:12.300
What did you just say to me, nephew?

01:35:13.200 --> 01:35:15.399
Godson.

01:35:15.400 --> 01:35:17.299
My blood!

01:35:17.300 --> 01:35:19.400
How dare you come to my house

01:35:19.500 --> 01:35:24.199
and tell me to get out?

01:35:24.200 --> 01:35:27.300
Have you no shame?

01:35:28.200 --> 01:35:30.299
You really think I'm
going to leave my house?

01:35:30.300 --> 01:35:33.400
My land?

01:35:34.200 --> 01:35:38.199
I have worked this earth too
hard with my bare hands

01:35:38.200 --> 01:35:40.200
to let some Fidelistas take it from me!

01:35:40.300 --> 01:35:41.300
Listen, you have to understand,

01:35:41.500 --> 01:35:42.400
this is the future now.

01:35:42.500 --> 01:35:43.400
The future?

01:35:43.500 --> 01:35:45.200
Yes, the future.

01:35:45.300 --> 01:35:46.400
Piss on your future!

01:35:46.500 --> 01:35:50.200
I spit on your future!

01:35:50.300 --> 01:35:52.300
Let them try and take it.

01:35:52.400 --> 01:35:55.300
You just let them try!

01:35:57.300 --> 01:35:58.499
Take it easy.

01:35:58.500 --> 01:36:00.299
Where is your sense of

