I'm sorry.

01:39:47.400 --> 01:39:49.200
I'm sorry.

01:41:33.200 --> 01:41:34.400
How could you?

01:41:34.500 --> 01:41:36.400
Look at me!

01:41:57.300 --> 01:42:02.399
What has become of you, Ricardo?

01:42:02.400 --> 01:42:05.399
You betray your country.

01:42:05.400 --> 01:42:10.200
You disgraced your family.

01:42:15.400 --> 01:42:17.500
You are lost, my son.

01:42:21.400 --> 01:42:24.400
Yes, you are.

01:42:39.400 --> 01:42:41.300
Fico.

01:43:12.400 --> 01:43:14.399
I wish I could go back to the beginning.

01:43:14.400 --> 01:43:17.300
Mmm, I love beginnings.

01:43:17.400 --> 01:43:18.400
Why's that?

01:43:18.401 --> 01:43:20.399
Nothing's happened yet.

01:43:20.400 --> 01:43:24.400
Anticipation is in the air. Optimism.

01:43:29.400 --> 01:43:31.300
What about the end?

01:43:31.400 --> 01:43:34.200
Well, they don't call
it the end for nothing.

01:43:34.300 --> 01:43:37.200
I hate endings...

01:43:37.300 --> 01:43:39.299
unless, of course, your
end is your beginning,

01:43:39.300 --> 01:43:42.199
Which makes your beginning your end.

01:43:42.200 --> 01:43:44.300
Then I would love the end.

01:43:44.400 --> 01:43:47.300
Where are we now?

01:43:48.200 --> 01:43:51.299
If you don't know where you are,

01:43:51.300 --> 01:43:53.300
then you are in the middle.

01:43:53.500 --> 01:43:55.300
No doubt about that.

01:45:21.200 --> 01:45:23.400
There goes my swing vote.

01:45:30.400 --> 01:45:34.200
Friends, I have an important
announcement to make.

01:45:34.400 --> 01:45:37.300
There's no dessert.

01:45:39.300 --> 01:45:42.299
Food rationing.

01:45:42.300 --> 01:45:43.400
Would you mind?

01:45:48.300 --> 01:45:53.199
And now a few brief words
from the man with no name?

01:45:53.200 --> 01:45:54.500
I'll be brief.

01:45:59.500 --> 01:46:03.300
Ladies and gentlemen...

01:46:05.400 --> 01:46:09.299
our Federico Fellove is
going away for good.

01:46:09.300 --> 01:46:11.399
Being a writer, I stress the word good

01:46:11.400 --> 01:46:14.200
because I think it will
be good for him...

01:46:14.300 --> 01:46:17.200
and good for us, too.

01:46:17.300 --> 01:46:20.200
Fico is going to New York City...

01:46:20.400 --> 01:46:23.399
the Mecca of show business...

01:46:23.400 --> 01:46:25.400
Where I'm gonna be
headin' for eventually.

01:46:28.200 --> 01:46:30.399
Fico, I know you're gonna be there

01:46:30.400 --> 01:46:32.199
to welcome us with open arms

01:46:32.200 --> 01:46:36.200
as you have so many times in the past.

01:46:49.300 --> 01:46:51.300
Ladies and gentlemen...

01:46:51.400 --> 01:46:53.400
the writer, for the
first time, speechless.

01:46:56.400 --> 01:46:59.200
I'll bail you out.

01:46:59.400 --> 01:47:00.300
I'd like to say something.

01:47:01.200 --> 01:47:02.400
Please.

01:47:08.300 --> 01:47:11.199
I wanna say that this, uh...

01:47:11.200 --> 01:47:14.400
this moment here means
a great deal to me...

01:47:14.500 --> 01:47:17.400
and I'm gonna treasure this forever.

01:47:22.200 --> 01:47:23.300
Salud.

01:47:27.300 --> 01:47:31.200
Forever is a very long time, Fico.

01:47:38.200 --> 01:47:40.200
It's all right. He's with me.

01:47:57.200 --> 01:47:59.199
Would you like a drink?

01:47:59.200 --> 01:48:00.499
No, I'm driving.

01:48:00.500 --> 01:48:03.299
I thought you came in a taxi.

01:48:03.300 --> 01:48:05.299
I'm driving the taxi.

01:48:05.300 --> 01:48:06.399
Very funny.

01:48:06.400 --> 01:48:08.299
Most things are these days.

01:48:08.300 --> 01:48:10.400
I need to speak to you alone.

01:48:23.300 --> 01:48:26.299
I have an exit visa.

01:48:26.300 --> 01:48:27.300
I'm leaving.

01:48:27.400 --> 01:48:30.199
What did you say? You heard what I said.

01:48:30.200 --> 01:48:32.300
I'm leaving the country.

01:48:32.500 --> 01:48:34.400
I want you to come with me.

01:48:35.300 --> 01:48:36.200
To go where?

01:48:36.300 --> 01:48:38.299
Anywhere but here. It doesn't matter.

01:48:38.300 --> 01:48:39.500
We can start again.

01:48:40.300 --> 01:48:44.199
Fico, I have a duty to my country.

01:48:44.200 --> 01:48:46.299
It is what Luis died for.

01:48:46.300 --> 01:48:50.300
Luis Luis died for Cuba.
He didn't die for Fidel.

01:48:54.200 --> 01:48:57.200
For the first time in my life,

01:48:57.300 --> 01:48:59.300
I feel I'm part of something important.

01:49:02.200 --> 01:49:05.200
I feel I can make a difference.

01:49:05.400 --> 01:49:07.300
We're fighting the just cause.

01:49:07.500 --> 01:49:09.299
In a ruthless and undemocratic manner.

01:49:09.300 --> 01:49:11.499
We have to make our reforms first.

01:49:11.500 --> 01:49:13.299
Democracy will come later.

01:49:13.300 --> 01:49:14.400
Then why not the other way around?

01:49:15.300 --> 01:49:16.399
I don't want to argue with you.

01:49:16.400 --> 01:49:19.299
Never you.

01:49:19.300 --> 01:49:22.399
Why don't you give us a chance?

01:49:22.400 --> 01:49:25.299
Us? Us as in us?

01:49:25.300 --> 01:49:27.399
Orus as in you and the cause calibre?

01:49:27.400 --> 01:49:29.200
Don't be angry with me.

01:49:29.300 --> 01:49:32.399
No, anger would be too simple.

01:49:32.400 --> 01:49:34.200
You must know that I love you.

01:49:35.400 --> 01:49:37.300
That's the complicated part.

01:49:38.400 --> 01:49:40.199
I'm sorry, Senora Fellove.

01:49:40.200 --> 01:49:43.299
The Commandante Guevara and the
Soviet ambassador want to see you.

01:49:43.300 --> 01:49:46.200
It seems urgent.

01:49:47.400 --> 01:49:49.299
Please stay.

01:49:49.300 --> 01:49:51.300
Why do you have to leave?

01:49:51.400 --> 01:49:53.200
Please.

01:50:14.400 --> 01:50:17.400
Miss Fellove, this is
the Soviet ambassador.

01:50:19.400 --> 01:50:21.200
That is all you're ever gonna get.

01:50:21.400 --> 01:50:23.399
What? It's not included in the deal?

01:50:23.400 --> 01:50:25.399
Yes.

01:50:25.400 --> 01:50:27.200
Let's go. Come on. Let's go.

01:50:27.400 --> 01:50:30.300
What are you doing?

01:50:31.200 --> 01:50:32.399
You're embarrassing me.

01:50:32.400 --> 01:50:34.300
This gathering is an embarrassment.

01:50:34.400 --> 01:50:36.199
Get your hands off me.

01:50:36.200 --> 01:50:37.200
Get you hands off me!

01:50:37.200 --> 01:50:38.200
Take your hands off me.

01:50:38.201 --> 01:50:39.400
You have something to say?

01:50:41.300 --> 01:50:43.300
Comrade...

01:50:43.500 --> 01:50:46.300
the dance floor is yours.

01:50:57.500 --> 01:51:01.299
To Luis Fellove...

01:51:01.300 --> 01:51:04.299
Who died for a dream,

01:51:04.300 --> 01:51:07.400
a dream of a pluralistic
and democratic Cuba!

01:51:11.300 --> 01:51:13.400
Long live a free Cuba.

01:51:22.300 --> 01:51:23.300
Let's go.

01:51:26.400 --> 01:51:28.299
Long live a free Cuba.

01:51:28.300 --> 01:51:30.200
Long live a free Cuba.

01:51:33.200 --> 01:51:34.300
Fico, wait.

01:51:34.400 --> 01:51:35.400
I can't leave.

01:51:35.401 --> 01:51:39.400
We must leave before it's
too late to get out.

01:51:40.300 --> 01:51:41.399
Try and understand.

01:51:41.400 --> 01:51:43.200
Try to understand?

01:51:43.300 --> 01:51:48.199
I understand that I'm lost without you.

01:51:48.200 --> 01:51:49.299
This is bigger than us.

01:51:49.300 --> 01:51:51.400
There is nothing bigger than us.

01:51:52.300 --> 01:51:54.200
Listen to me.

01:51:54.300 --> 01:51:57.300
Can't you see what's happening?

01:51:57.500 --> 01:52:00.299
You're being taken advantage of.

01:52:00.300 --> 01:52:02.299
Is that what you want?

01:52:02.300 --> 01:52:05.399
You want to be told what to
think the rest of your life?

01:52:05.400 --> 01:52:09.200
Because there's no end to this.

01:52:09.300 --> 01:52:12.300
This is madness.

01:52:12.400 --> 01:52:14.400
You deserve more. We deserve more.

01:52:18.300 --> 01:52:22.200
If you stay, your life
will not belong to you.

01:52:23.500 --> 01:52:25.300
Please.

01:52:28.400 --> 01:52:30.300
Come with me.

01:52:39.500 --> 01:52:41.400
Please.

01:52:44.400 --> 01:52:46.400
We're all that's left of our family.

01:52:50.400 --> 01:52:52.299
In time, you'll understand.

01:52:52.300 --> 01:52:54.300
There's no more time.

01:53:00.400 --> 01:53:02.400
Here's your exit visa.

01:53:05.200 --> 01:53:08.300
I'm leaving tomorrow at
5:00 in the afternoon.

01:54:13.300 --> 01:54:14.300
Comrade, companero.

01:54:15.400 --> 01:54:16.499
I salute you.

01:54:16.500 --> 01:54:18.399
On behalf of our maximum leader

01:54:18.400 --> 01:54:21.200
and all Communists in Cuba, welcome!
Bienvenido!

01:54:37.400 --> 01:54:41.299
Federico Junior.

01:54:41.300 --> 01:54:44.300
I want you to have this.

01:54:47.400 --> 01:54:50.299
You will need it on the day where...

01:54:50.300 --> 01:54:54.300
when what is left of our family...

01:54:54.400 --> 01:54:57.399
be reunited.

01:54:57.400 --> 01:54:59.299
That's for you. Mother and I.

01:54:59.300 --> 01:55:02.299
Just don't worry because
well be right here.

01:55:02.300 --> 01:55:04.399
We're strong people.

01:55:04.400 --> 01:55:07.299
We're gonna be right here...

01:55:07.300 --> 01:55:09.400
waiting for you.

01:55:09.500 --> 01:55:12.299
We'll have dinner together.

01:55:12.300 --> 01:55:16.400
Uh, but what is very important...

01:55:17.300 --> 01:55:19.400
At 6, okay?

01:55:19.500 --> 01:55:20.400
Sharp.

01:55:20.500 --> 01:55:22.400
Not a minute afterwards.

01:55:22.500 --> 01:55:24.300
That's my boy.

01:55:42.300 --> 01:55:45.199
Yeah. That's it.

01:55:45.200 --> 01:55:50.100
There. Lt fits you as well
as it fits your father.

01:55:50.200 --> 01:55:51.299
Are you kidding?

01:55:51.300 --> 01:55:53.299
Much better.

01:55:53.300 --> 01:55:54.500
Look at him.

01:56:08.300 --> 01:56:11.200
I'm gonna send for you as soon as I can.

01:56:14.400 --> 01:56:16.400
Bye.

01:56:26.400 --> 01:56:29.300
It's all okay.

01:56:43.200 --> 01:56:44.300
God bless you.

01:56:53.200 --> 01:56:54.200
I gotta go.

01:56:54.201 --> 01:56:55.300
Okay.

01:56:58.400 --> 01:57:00.200
We'll be here.

01:58:32.300 --> 01:58:33.400
Let's go!

01:58:33.500 --> 01:58:34.400
Next.

01:58:38.300 --> 01:58:39.300
What's in the bag?

01:58:39.301 --> 01:58:40.399
Only what I need.

01:58:40.400 --> 01:58:42.200
Open it.

01:58:52.300 --> 01:58:54.300
Man of taste.

01:58:56.300 --> 01:58:57.399
What's this?

01:58:57.400 --> 01:59:00.299
Home movies. There's my camera.

01:59:00.300 --> 01:59:02.300
Open it.

01:59:06.300 --> 01:59:09.400
I wanna photograph the
injustice of American life.

01:59:13.300 --> 01:59:14.400
Stretch out your arms.

01:59:19.200 --> 01:59:21.200
Empty your pockets.

01:59:24.300 --> 01:59:27.200
Ring and watch, take them off.

01:59:34.500 --> 01:59:36.299
Put it in here.

01:59:36.300 --> 01:59:38.300
Sir?

01:59:45.300 --> 01:59:47.300
Inside.

01:59:49.300 --> 01:59:50.200
Take it off.

01:59:55.400 --> 01:59:58.299
This watch belonged to my father.

01:59:58.300 --> 02:00:00.200
Belonged is correct.

02:00:00.300 --> 02:00:01.400
In here.

02:00:04.500 --> 02:00:07.299
What's this?

02:00:07.300 --> 02:00:08.300
A memento.

02:00:08.301 --> 02:00:09.400
Hmm.

02:00:10.300 --> 02:00:13.299
You worms are strange.

02:00:13.300 --> 02:00:16.300
Not yet gone, and you're
already carrying souvenirs.

02:00:18.300 --> 02:00:21.400
You can't take Cuba with you, you know.

02:00:21.500 --> 02:00:23.300
Free to go.

02:00:24.400 --> 02:00:26.200
Next.

02:02:15.200 --> 02:02:17.299
This is Willis Conover
of the Voice of America

02:02:17.300 --> 02:02:19.299
bringing you The Music of Freedom.

02:02:19.300 --> 02:02:22.199
For those of you in limbo
out there, here is the Duke

02:02:22.200 --> 02:02:24.199
and saxophone is Coleman Hawkins.

02:02:24.200 --> 02:02:26.300
With Limbo Jazz.

02:03:11.400 --> 02:03:13.300
Who is it?

02:03:13.400 --> 02:03:15.300
Room service.

02:03:28.200 --> 02:03:29.300
So when did you leave?

02:03:31.400 --> 02:03:34.199
Better ask when did I escape.

02:03:34.200 --> 02:03:37.300
Semantics, my friend,
is made up of antics.

02:03:38.400 --> 02:03:40.400
I'm glad to see you.

02:03:42.200 --> 02:03:44.200
It can only mean that you're lonely.

02:03:44.400 --> 02:03:46.499
Lonely is the best word.

02:03:46.500 --> 02:03:48.400
When a man is truly lonely,

02:03:48.500 --> 02:03:51.200
even a light bulb is good company.

02:03:53.300 --> 02:03:56.199
Actually, I'm masquerading as an exile.

02:03:56.200 --> 02:03:58.299
Well, your impersonation is quite good.

02:03:58.300 --> 02:03:59.300
I'm still in Cuba.

02:04:00.500 --> 02:04:02.500
Where do you think I am, Jersey City?

02:04:08.200 --> 02:04:10.299
Joe DiMaggio.

02:04:10.300 --> 02:04:12.400
Minnie Minoso.

02:04:17.400 --> 02:04:18.400
He looks in.

02:04:18.500 --> 02:04:21.400
Yeah, you latched on that one.

02:04:25.300 --> 02:04:27.300
Hmm, where we going?

02:04:27.500 --> 02:04:28.400
El Dragon Rojo,

02:04:28.500 --> 02:04:31.400
a Cuban-Chinese restaurant
which is neither.

02:04:31.500 --> 02:04:34.300
But they are under the
illusion I'm a writer.

02:04:34.400 --> 02:04:35.400
Madam.

02:04:37.300 --> 02:04:38.200
Oh, madam.

02:04:38.400 --> 02:04:40.399
What would you like today?

02:04:40.400 --> 02:04:42.200
My usual please.

02:04:42.400 --> 02:04:43.400
Beluga caviar to start.

02:04:43.401 --> 02:04:45.399
For an entre, pheasant tongues

02:04:45.400 --> 02:04:47.399
marinated in vin de sauternes.

02:04:47.400 --> 02:04:48.400
Smyrna figs for dessert,

02:04:49.300 --> 02:04:50.200
and a bottle of Veuve Cliquot

02:04:50.201 --> 02:04:52.500
chilled, not merely cold, please.

02:04:53.300 --> 02:04:55.399
Fried rice and bananas for two.

02:04:55.400 --> 02:04:57.299
Yes, the special, please,
but bring it right away.

02:04:57.300 --> 02:04:59.399
We haven't eaten since the revolution.

02:04:59.400 --> 02:05:03.200
Did you know that Cuba is half white,

02:05:03.300 --> 02:05:05.400
half black, and half Chinese?

02:05:06.200 --> 02:05:07.300
That's three halves.

02:05:07.400 --> 02:05:09.400
Everything is coming in threes
these days, even halves.

02:05:10.300 --> 02:05:11.300
Which half are you?

02:05:11.301 --> 02:05:13.300
Half owner.

02:05:16.300 --> 02:05:17.400
Should have been a stand-up comedian.

02:05:18.200 --> 02:05:20.200
I may hold you to that.

02:05:20.300 --> 02:05:21.200
I can't help you.

02:05:21.300 --> 02:05:23.200
I'm just a former cabaret owner.

02:05:23.300 --> 02:05:25.199
Once a cabaret owner,
always a cabaret owner.

02:05:25.200 --> 02:05:28.200
Oris it once a former cabaret owner,

02:05:28.300 --> 02:05:30.400
always a former cabaret owner?

02:05:45.200 --> 02:05:47.199
Fico.

02:05:47.200 --> 02:05:48.300
Take a break, chico.

02:05:48.400 --> 02:05:50.300
Time to suffer.

02:05:50.400 --> 02:05:52.399
Good one.

02:05:52.400 --> 02:05:53.400
Thank you.

02:05:53.400 --> 02:05:54.400
Ahem.

02:05:56.300 --> 02:05:57.200
Thank you.

02:05:57.300 --> 02:05:58.200
Look, Fico,

02:05:58.300 --> 02:06:00.199
I've been...

02:06:00.200 --> 02:06:01.400
I've been thinking.

02:06:06.400 --> 02:06:10.399
You know, it bothers me

02:06:10.400 --> 02:06:13.399
to see you, Fico Fellove,

02:06:13.400 --> 02:06:15.199
Working in the kitchen.

02:06:15.200 --> 02:06:16.299
Nonsense.

02:06:16.300 --> 02:06:18.400
Now, I've told you before
I appreciate the work.

02:06:19.300 --> 02:06:21.399
Well, anyway, I was thinking.

02:06:21.400 --> 02:06:25.299
What if I set up a piano in the cafe?

02:06:25.300 --> 02:06:27.300
Would you be interested in...

02:06:29.300 --> 02:06:32.499
Unfortunately, the pay would be the same,

02:06:32.500 --> 02:06:35.300
but plus tips.

02:06:35.400 --> 02:06:37.399
Whatever you need. Hmm?

02:06:37.400 --> 02:06:39.200
You know I appreciate it.

02:06:39.400 --> 02:06:40.300
Mm.

02:06:40.400 --> 02:06:42.200
I'd like to keep this job, too.

02:06:42.400 --> 02:06:43.300
I need the extra money.

02:06:43.400 --> 02:06:44.400
I'm trying to bring my family.

02:06:45.200 --> 02:06:47.200
Enough said. Enough said.

02:06:47.400 --> 02:06:48.300
To free Cuba.

02:06:48.400 --> 02:06:50.300
Salud. Salud.

02:06:58.500 --> 02:07:01.400
The present you are living in is so thin,

02:07:01.500 --> 02:07:03.400
you could squeeze it underneath a door.

02:07:03.500 --> 02:07:06.299
The trouble with exile is exile.

02:07:06.300 --> 02:07:07.300
Thank you.

02:07:07.301 --> 02:07:09.200
I have a solution.

02:07:09.400 --> 02:07:13.199
This pretty lady's torch
is Aladdin's lamp.

02:07:13.200 --> 02:07:16.199
Aladdin's lamp.

02:07:16.200 --> 02:07:18.199
And it will grant any wish in your life.

02:07:18.200 --> 02:07:19.299
I wish I could relive it.

02:07:19.300 --> 02:07:22.300
You can by rebuilding it.

02:07:22.400 --> 02:07:24.400
Will you work for me?

02:07:25.300 --> 02:07:28.300
Free drinks?

02:07:28.400 --> 02:07:29.400
Done.

02:07:32.400 --> 02:07:35.300
Gentlemen, time to suffer.

02:07:44.300 --> 02:07:46.300
The door was open.

02:07:48.300 --> 02:07:49.400
You know, the thing I
love most about New York

02:07:50.300 --> 02:07:53.399
is that you're always
running into old friends.

02:07:53.400 --> 02:07:56.300
You know why we're friends?

02:07:59.500 --> 02:08:01.400
Because we don't believe in coincidences.

02:08:01.500 --> 02:08:03.300
Please sit down.

02:08:20.200 --> 02:08:21.400
You may consider me an enemy,

02:08:21.500 --> 02:08:24.399
but I've always considered
you a friend, Federico.

02:08:24.400 --> 02:08:28.299
I may at times have lost
my patience at times,

02:08:28.300 --> 02:08:30.299
but never with a man I respect

02:08:30.300 --> 02:08:32.300
and that respects me in kind.

02:08:35.300 --> 02:08:37.199
How we doing there, Joe?

02:08:37.200 --> 02:08:39.299
Flirting. Good.

02:08:39.300 --> 02:08:40.300
Take your hat off.

02:08:44.300 --> 02:08:47.399
Ah, she was a beautiful thing, Havana.

02:08:47.400 --> 02:08:50.199
We should have known she was a...

02:08:50.200 --> 02:08:51.300
a heartbreaker.

02:08:54.200 --> 02:08:56.200
And here we are.

02:08:56.300 --> 02:08:58.400
It's bashert destiny.

02:09:02.500 --> 02:09:04.499
Now, listen.

02:09:04.500 --> 02:09:06.399
Listen hard.

02:09:06.400 --> 02:09:08.400
I didn't bomb your place, kid.

02:09:08.500 --> 02:09:09.400
That's not my style.

02:09:16.300 --> 02:09:17.400
Okay?

02:09:19.400 --> 02:09:21.200
May I have an egg cream?

02:09:21.300 --> 02:09:23.200
Chocolate syrup, cold milk.

02:09:23.400 --> 02:09:25.300
Spritz the seltzer until
it foams up over the top.

02:09:25.400 --> 02:09:26.400
No.

02:09:27.300 --> 02:09:28.200
And a bit of rum, yes?

02:09:28.300 --> 02:09:29.400
Yeah. An egg cream.

02:09:33.300 --> 02:09:34.500
What's your name?

02:09:35.300 --> 02:09:37.400
I never thought you'd ask.

02:09:39.200 --> 02:09:41.199
My offer's still open.

02:09:41.200 --> 02:09:44.399
A new club. Las Vegas.

02:09:44.400 --> 02:09:46.300
Nevada. No humidity.

02:09:46.400 --> 02:09:49.199
Don't answer. Think about it.

02:09:49.200 --> 02:09:50.300
You know?

02:09:50.400 --> 02:09:53.299
You know, even in rejection

02:09:53.300 --> 02:09:56.399
lead me on a little bit, hmm?

02:09:56.400 --> 02:09:59.399
Don't break my heart...

02:09:59.400 --> 02:10:01.200
just yet.

02:10:05.400 --> 02:10:08.199
You like egg cream.

02:10:08.200 --> 02:10:10.199
Yes, I like egg creams.

02:10:10.200 --> 02:10:13.300
And I'm not crazy about humidity, either.

02:10:18.300 --> 02:10:21.400
You give my regards to your family.

02:10:25.300 --> 02:10:28.399
You have the ingredients right.

02:10:28.400 --> 02:10:30.500
There's an art with the seltzer spritz.

02:10:31.200 --> 02:10:32.399
Your chocolate goes at the bottom.

02:10:32.400 --> 02:10:34.199
With milk over it,

02:10:34.200 --> 02:10:36.199
and then you spritz straight down,

02:10:36.200 --> 02:10:39.200
but then you spritz around the glass

02:10:39.400 --> 02:10:41.400
until it rises to the top.

02:10:43.300 --> 02:10:45.199
Always a pleasure, Lansky.

02:10:45.200 --> 02:10:47.200
I mean Mr. Meyer. Love your wieners.

02:10:54.300 --> 02:10:55.400
Bueno, Fico. Good night.

02:10:56.300 --> 02:10:57.300
Okay, have a good time.

02:10:57.301 --> 02:11:00.299
Keys are in the back. Have a good time.

02:11:00.300 --> 02:11:02.400
Good night, Mrs. Calabash,
wherever you are.

02:11:02.500 --> 02:11:05.300
Gentlemen, don't burn the place down.

02:11:32.200 --> 02:11:34.199
Did you ever have the feeling

02:11:34.200 --> 02:11:35.300
that you wanted to go?

02:11:38.200 --> 02:11:39.300
Did you ever have the feeling

02:11:39.400 --> 02:11:41.199
that you wanted to stay?

02:11:41.200 --> 02:11:45.299
Go, stay, go, stay, go...

02:11:45.300 --> 02:11:47.299
ooh.

02:11:47.300 --> 02:11:49.400
That's a go, isn't it?

02:11:51.500 --> 02:11:54.299
Madam, always a pleasure.

02:11:54.300 --> 02:11:56.300
Give my regards to the pigeons.

02:12:12.400 --> 02:12:13.400
Why are you here?

02:12:13.500 --> 02:12:17.300
I'm here...

02:12:17.400 --> 02:12:19.400
with our dedication to United Nations.

02:12:23.400 --> 02:12:25.400
Do you have time for some coffee?

02:12:43.300 --> 02:12:44.300
I'm sorry you left.

02:12:46.400 --> 02:12:48.399
There was nothing left for me in Havana.

02:12:48.400 --> 02:12:51.199
Yes, I know.

02:12:51.200 --> 02:12:52.200
You lost your club.

02:12:52.300 --> 02:12:54.299
No, that's not what I meant.

02:12:54.300 --> 02:12:56.299
You sound bitter.

02:12:56.300 --> 02:12:58.399
Not at all.

02:12:58.400 --> 02:13:00.300
I have no money...

02:13:02.400 --> 02:13:05.299
but I feel...

02:13:05.300 --> 02:13:07.399
as though I'm worth more than I ever was.

02:13:07.400 --> 02:13:09.400
Would it do any good to say I'm sorry?

02:13:10.200 --> 02:13:11.299
No, not really.

02:13:11.300 --> 02:13:13.200
Try at least to understand me.

02:13:13.300 --> 02:13:16.199
I've understood more
than you could explain.

02:13:16.200 --> 02:13:19.399
Why don't you come back to Cuba with me?

02:13:19.400 --> 02:13:22.399
Because it's dangerous...

02:13:22.400 --> 02:13:24.199
for my soul.

02:13:24.200 --> 02:13:26.400
I see you still do not believe in causes.

02:13:30.400 --> 02:13:32.300
Well, I don't have a
loyalty to a lost cause.

02:13:35.500 --> 02:13:39.400
But I do have a loyalty to a lost city.

02:13:41.400 --> 02:13:44.400
And that's my cause and my curse.

02:13:45.200 --> 02:13:46.300
Please don't hate me, then.

02:13:46.400 --> 02:13:48.200
I'll never hate you.

02:13:55.500 --> 02:13:57.300
I'll always love you.

02:13:59.400 --> 02:14:01.400
Why can't you love me there?

02:14:01.500 --> 02:14:04.200
Too big of a price to pay.

02:14:23.200 --> 02:14:24.300
Be well.

02:14:28.400 --> 02:14:30.200
Stop crying.

02:14:34.300 --> 02:14:36.200
You can always love me here.

02:14:38.200 --> 02:14:39.200
Remember that.

02:14:47.400 --> 02:14:48.400
You're so beautiful.
